==English==
===Adverb===
'''why not?'''

#Why is that not true?
#:''I don't want to go out today. &mdash; Why not?''
#(''[[rhetorical]]'') Used to state that one has no objection to and approves of a proposal.
#:''Let's have pizza for lunch. &mdash; Yes, why not?''
#Used to introduce a proposal.
#:''Why not try turning the handle in the other direction to see if that opens the window?''

====Synonyms====
*(''why is that not true''): [[why]]?
*(''to show one has no objection''): [[all right]], [[I don't see why not]], [[OK]]
*(''to introduce a proposal''): [[how about]], [[what if]]

